      "role": "user",
      "content": "The stats you mentioned are pretty striking. When you look at the literature specifically regarding the higher rates in certain groups, how often do researchers argue that these are actually driven by inherent cultural or behavioral traits of those specific demographics, versus just being a result of socioeconomic factors? I'm looking for the arguments that emphasize the internal group dynamics/traits side of the discussion.",
